
[1]impassioned

   IMPAS'SIONED, a. Actuated or agitated by passion.

   The tempter all impassioned, thus began.

   1. Animated; excited; having the feelings warmed; as an impassioned
   orator.

   2. Animated; expressive of passion or ardor; as an impassioned
   discourse.
